Endpoint Endpoint Class

In this Article

Edit

CDN endpoint is the entity within a CDN profile containing configuration information such as origin, protocol, content caching and delivery behavior. The CDN endpoint uses the URL format <endpointname>.azureedge.net.

Properties summary

ContentTypesToCompress
ContentTypesToCompress

Gets or sets list of content types on which compression applies. The value should be a valid MIME type.
GeoFilters
GeoFilters

Gets or sets list of rules defining user geo access within a CDN endpoint. Each geo filter defines an acess rule to a specified path or content, e.g. block APAC for path /pictures/
HostName
HostName

Gets the host name of the endpoint structured as {endpointName}.{DNSZone}, e.g. consoto.azureedge.net
IsCompressionEnabled
IsCompressionEnabled

Gets or sets indicates whether content compression is enabled on CDN. Default value is false. If compression is enabled, content will be served as compressed if user requests for a compressed version. Content won't be compressed on CDN when requested content is smaller than 1 byte or larger than 1 MB.
IsHttpAllowed
IsHttpAllowed

Gets or sets indicates whether HTTP traffic is allowed on the endpoint. Default value is true. At least one protocol (HTTP or HTTPS) must be allowed.
IsHttpsAllowed
IsHttpsAllowed

Gets or sets indicates whether HTTPS traffic is allowed on the endpoint. Default value is true. At least one protocol (HTTP or HTTPS) must be allowed.
OptimizationType
OptimizationType

Gets or sets customer can specify what scenario they want this CDN endpoint to optimize, e.g. Download, Media services. With this information we can apply scenario driven optimization.
OriginHostHeader
OriginHostHeader

Gets or sets the host header CDN sends along with content requests to origin. The default value is the host name of the origin.
OriginPath
OriginPath

Gets or sets the path used when CDN sends request to origin.
Origins
Origins

Gets or sets the source of the content being delivered via CDN.
ProvisioningState
ProvisioningState

Gets provisioning status of the endpoint.
QueryStringCachingBehavior
QueryStringCachingBehavior

Gets or sets defines the query string caching behavior. Possible values include: 'IgnoreQueryString', 'BypassCaching', 'UseQueryString', 'NotSet'
ResourceState
ResourceState

Gets resource status of the endpoint. Possible values include: 'Creating', 'Deleting', 'Running', 'Starting', 'Stopped', 'Stopping'
